## Disclaimer
This report and any supplements are {{.classification}} and may be protected by one
or more legal privileges. It is intended solely for the use of the addressee
identified in the report. If you are not the intended recipient, any use,
disclosure, copying or distribution of the report is UNAUTHORIZED. If you have
received this report in error, please destroy it immediately.

In this particular project, a timebox approach was used to define the consulting
effort. This means that Cyber Controls allotted a prearranged amount of time to
one of its assessors to identify, document and assess vulnerabilities. Because
of this, there is no guarantee that the project has identified all possible
vulnerabilities and risks caused by them. Furthermore, this assessment is only
an immediate evaluation of the situation at the time the assessment was
performed. An evaluation of future security levels or possible future
vulnerabilities or risks caused by them may not be derived from it.

## Note Regarding Manual Testing
An assessment may involve manual testing. Manual testing is dependent on the
skills of the assessor and may carry a bias in terms of the scripts that the
assessor could use. No amount of assessment, in no mode and depth, can expose
all the innate vulnerabilities. These types of assessments are intended to find
the most fundamental of vulnerabilities and even then, not all vulnerabilities
may be exposed.

## Note Regarding Automated Testing
An assessment may involve the use of non-commercial or commercial scanning tools
(e.g., Network Scanners, (Web) Application Scanners) for automated testing. These
scans are provided on an “As Is, As Available” basis without any warranty of any
kind. By accepting this report, you understand that assessing security is highly
complex and changeable. Scanning tools make no warranty that their provided
service will find all vulnerabilities in an assessment object, or that the
solutions suggested and advice provided in the report will be complete or
error-free.
